Title: ActionSurface
Description: ActionSurface allows you to easily create action games based on the spritesurface class. You define platforms, walls, enemies, the character, his gun, etc, and ActionSurface takes care of the rest.
Author: Dan Vanderkam

Title: Alternate Highlight Colors
Description: Alternate Highlight Colors
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Array_Listbox_Sorting_Rb2
Description: A class that implements QuickSort and BubbleSort. It can sort any type of data: You need to subclass this class and then implement a Compare and a Swap function. The Sort class does the rest for you. It comes with lightly documented source and demonstration code.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Micono RbImageAxisTrans
Description: A plugin for REALbasic 2.1 which packages image axis transform such as flip horizontal
Author: Michio Ono

Title: BasicHTTP
Description:
BasicHTTP is a REALbasic class implementing the HTTP protocol. HTTP is the protocol used on the web.

I've written this class because I feel the existing class, Dan Vanderkam's wonderful httpSocket, has become outdated.
Author: Navdeep Bains

Title: Basic Strings.c
Description: C Class for manipulating string
Author: NoahFex

Title: Bigscroller
Description: BigScroller.rb was adapted from Apple code of the same name. It works in a similar fashion except for the lineStep and pageStep values.

Title: ButtonSpread
Description: The ButtonSpread class is used to present a matrix or "spread" of bevel buttons, checkboxes, or radio buttons.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Canvaspaint
Description: This class allows you to add excellent painting abilities to your program with next to no effort.
Author: Dan Vanderkam

Title: Counttimer
Description: This class is a subset of the timer class and can be used to make counters that count up or down for audio related projects
Author: Benjamin J. Schneider

Title: Crypto
Description: RC4 and SHA1 Implementations
Author: Matthijs van Duin

Title: CSMemoryPlug
Description: Catalyst Software has created this REALbasic plugin to give RB programmers some needed functions.  These functions all relate to the Memory Manager from the Mac toolbox.  Some may be standard Memory Manager functions, while others are combinations of Memory Manager routines.  You are free to use this plugin in your applications and are not required to pay Catalyst Software.  It would be nice if you mentioned us or gave us a copy of your program, but it is not necessary.  If you would like to use the source to this plugin for your own projects, you may do so.  If you modify the source and plan to redistribute the source, please mention us in the code somewhere.  Thank you for supporting Catalyst Software.

Title: dmGraphicUtilities Plugin
Description: Converts data strings to pictures, scrolling rect and Postscript functions.
Author: Stephan

Title: DoubleclickListbox
Description: This is a custom Listbox subclass that adds a CellDoubleClick event that is fired when a cell is double clicked.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Dynamic Formula
Description: An RbScript subclass which can be used to allow end users to enter in their own variables and values which you, the developer, can use as a dynamic formula which is embedded into your code. If that makes any sense....

Title: easyPalette
Description: easyPalette is a set of REALbasic classes that make it fast and easy to add cross platform tearoff floating palettes to your REALbasic project. The palette windows can contain grid style selection palettes of the type commonly used to select colors, patterns, line widths, arrow styles, "tools" and objects. In fact almost any kind of data that needs to be displayed and selected in a grid can be used with easyPalette.
Author: Peter Zegelin

Title: easyPalette
Description: easyPalette is a set of REALbasic classes that make it fast and easy to add cross platform tearoff floating palettes to your REALbasic project. The palette windows can contain grid style selection palettes of the type commonly used to select colors, patterns, line widths, arrow styles, "tools" and objects. In fact almost any kind of data that needs to be displayed and selected in a grid can be used with easyPalette.
Author: Peter Zegelin

Title: EasyPOP3
Description: EasyPOP3 is a POP3 socket. POP3 is the most common protocol used to access email.
Author: Navdeep Bains

Title: FFT_Plugin
Description:
FFT_Plugin allow calculation of 8bit or 16 bits data_blocks from 8 to 16384
samples.
Author: Didier Cugy

Title: Flame Library
Description: This is a port of the "Flame" code written by Kyle Ellrott in July of '98. It works, but it isn't a complete port nor a direct one. It has been completely rewritten and has a smarter algorithm to speed it up.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSAutoComplete Simple
Description: An editfield class to allow autocompletion in single line editfields.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: DoubleclickListbox
Description: This is a custom control which appears and behaves like the +/- buttons found in certain places in Mac OS X such as the Accounts preference pane in System Preferences.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fscursormodule
Description: Module that auotmoatically balances showing and hiding of the cursor when using ShowCursor and HideCursor and also provides ObscureCursor as well as the new Carbon/OS X feature (I'm not sure which) ShieldCursor which blocks the cursor from being visible in the specified area.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsdictionarytodisk
Description: An exemplified module which takes a dictionary and writes it to disk or loads a dictionary from disk.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsdisclosurebutton
Description: Implements the new disclosure button control in OS X.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSExtractMovieSound 1.0
Description: A plugin that will grab the sound from any quicktime compatable movie or sound file.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fskiosk
Description: FSKiosk is module that utilizes new functionality in Mac OS X 10.3 which enables developers to easily take some of the necessary steps to develop a kiosk application. Free, requires 10.3 since it doesn't do anything on 10.2 (but I believe it still runs).
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsmetalbutton
Description: FSMetalButton is a custom canvas subclass which creates metal buttons which work wonderfully on metal windows in Mac OS X.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSMovieExtension 1.0
Description: Adds methods to the movie class to determine length position whether it is playing or not etc…
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSNotification 2.0
Description: FSNotification is a plugin that interfaces with the Notification Manager. You can use FSN to get attention of users when they are in another application. You have the choice of Flashing your application's icon in the Application menu with or without sound and, an alert box with your text with or without sound.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fspicturefonts
Description: FSPictureFonts is a module which enables developers to draw a string using a "picture font." This is extremely useful for games.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsplayqtmovie
Description: Allows you to play movies without using a movie player. Mainly for playing MIDI files which will only open using a movie player.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsrelevancebar
Description: Implements the new relevance bar control in OS X.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsresizepic
Description: A small module which resizes a picture.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsscrollingcalendar
Description: FSScrollingCalendar is the premiere solution for interactive calendars in REALbasic applications.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fssound
Description: FSSound is a small plugin that allows you to record a sound to a file.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSToolboxSheetWee 1.0
Description: A plugin project combination which works around current icks in Carbon allowing you to drag objects from a sheet to the sheet's parent. Useful in customizeable toolbar type stuff.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSThumbnailView v1.0
Description: Originally part of a custom application I was developing for a client, FSThumbnailView is a canvas subclass that displays a collection of images in a thumbnail view similar to iPhoto but also can draw them in a thumbnail list view.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fstilepic
Description: A small module which tiles a picture.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fstruncate
Description: A module which will take a string and truncate it to a specific pixel or character width by either chopping off the end or squishing out the middle.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Fsurlmanager
Description: Contains useful methods (currently only 1) that offer URL manipulation and whatnot.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSWindowState 1.0
Description: A small plugin which allows you to place the dimple in the close widget of a window under OS X and sets the state of the proxy icon under classic - these are used to show that the window has been modified since it was last saved.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: FSZoomRects
Description: A module which show zoom rects.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: GroupBoxPro Plugin 1.0
Description: GroupBoxPro Plugin is a plugin for REALbasic from (http://www.realsoftware.com) that adds a control to REALbasic that has two different GroupBox Interfaces, It also allows you to use icons and color text.
Author: Shane Morton

Title: HyperCard Buttons 1.0
Description: HyperCard Buttons 1.0

Title: HotlineSocketLite
Description: Hotline Protocol for REALBasic
Author: Jason Toffaletti

Title: Hsh_Hashtable
Description: RB 2 & 3: HSH_HashTable is a package that implements a simple static hash table as a replacement for REALbasic's built-in collection class. Retrieving an object from a hsh_HashTable is about 40 times faster than from a collection.
Author: Erich Rast

Title: httpSocket 2.0
Description: httpSocket provides a simple, effective, and easy way to use the http protocol through Realbasic.
Author: Dan Vanderkam

Title: HTVCPSocket 2.1.2
Description: This class lets you use HTVCP (HyperText Version Checking Protocol) easily, and with a minimum of hassle and fuss.
Author: Toby W. Rush

Title: IcnsReader Module v1.0
Description: This module contains cross-platform code to read a large 128x128 icon from an icns file. Please contribute if you'd like!
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Lingo2
Description: A complete and easily expandable scripting language for RB. This allows you to give users of your program much more power.
Author: Dan Vanderkam

Title: Lingo2 Source
Description: A complete and easily expandable scripting language for RB. This allows you to give users of your program much more power.
Author: Dan Vanderkam

Title: Lingoscript
Description: LingoScript is a module that provides scripting capabilities to realbasic. This means that you can allow users of your program to write their own programs (scripts) from in your app. This allows you to give users of your program lots of power over it.
Author: Dan Vanderkam

Title: Madplug12
Description: MADPlug is a plugin for REALbasic which allows developers to play back SoundTracker format music files. It makes use of the PlayerPro MADLibrary, written by Antoine Rosset.

Title: Madplug2
Description: MADPlug is a plugin for REALbasic which allows developers to play back SoundTracker format music files. It makes use of the PlayerPro MADLibrary, written by Antoine Rosset.

Title: Movieplayer_Plugin
Description: MoviePlayer Applies to RealBasic 2.1 or more recent running on Mac PPC, Mac OSX and Win platforms. MoviePlayer extend the Movie Player Control and now the Movie Class.
Author: Didier Cugy

Title: MPCP Networking for REALbasic
Description: MPCP Socket 1.0 classes are a bundle of classes and modules that allow you to easily transfer arbitrary binary data over sockets. MPCP is a highly extendable, flexible protocol and supports so-called threaded commands.
Author: Erich Rast

Title: Nlb
Description: Netscape-like button class
Author: Michio Ono

Title: PictCanvas 1.0
Description: PICTCanvas is an RB class that displays pictures or picture files dropped on it. It has some basic button functionality (sticky and normal) and can allow scrolling with the mouse if the picture is larger than the canvas itself.
Author: Erich Rast

Title: Picturestringextensions
Description: The PictureStringExtensions module extends the Picture and String classes with methods to add converting a picture to or from a string.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: PlaceholderField v1.0
Description: A simple class which displays a placeholder string in gray text in the field when there's no text in the field. An example of this is "Google" in the search field of Safari.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: QTAudioPlayer
Description: This class is a subclass of the MoviePlayer class with enhanced audio functions. QTAudioPlayer supports Mac OS 8.5 through Mac OS X with QuckTime 4.0 or higher.
Author: Benjamin J. Schneider

Title: Quicktime FileTransfer (Demo)
Description: QTFT or QuickTime FileTransfer allows the transfer of remote files to local files, including the transfer of files into REALbasic's virtual volumes and out. The crux of this plugin is to transfer the files asynchroneously and as quickly as possible. This plugin is a rewrite of our older QTFileTransfer plugin.

Description: QTFT or QuickTime FileTransfer allows the transfer of remote files to local files, including the transfer of files into REALbasic's virtual volumes and out. The crux of this plugin is to transfer the files asynchroneously and as quickly as possible. This plugin is a rewrite of our older QTFileTransfer plugin.

Author: Michio Ono

Author: Michio Ono

Description: RB Helper, is an Open Source project that has many features that are useful to almost any RB programmer. If you have a good idea for improving RB Helper, you can add it yourself and submit the improvement to me
Author: Theodore H.Smith

Title: Micono IconLocation
Description: Get and Set an icon location.
Author: Michio Ono

Author: Michio Ono

Author: Michio Ono

Author: Michio Ono

Author: Michio Ono

Author: Michio Ono

Description: Open any PPC-enabled RB Plugin with this tool to see what Controls, Classes and Methods it provides.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Micono ScreenCapature v1.1.0b1
Description: Rb plugin for screen capture.
Author: Michio Ono

Title: RbStringUtil
Description: String utiltiies
Author: Michio Ono

Title: FTP Socket Subclass
Description: Contains modules/classes for accessing and tranferring files through FTP.
Author: Brian F. Jones

Title: Rounded Editfield 1.0
Description: A canvas subclass which can be used to make rounded editfields in REALbasic applications.

Title: SimpleCMD_Socket
Description: SimpleCMD_Socket 0.5 is a socket class you can use to send & receive arbitrary commands with as many arguments of arbitrary length you want. You just create a new instance of an accompanied class called Socket_Command, append your arguments as strings and send it. The other host will receive a copy of your command--- that's all.
Author: Erich Rast

Title: SearchField Plugin 1.0b3
Description: This plugin implements the rounded search field commonly found in applications on Mac OS X. It requires Mac OS X 10.3 both when developing an application and when the final application is run. The control also only works in Mach-O built applications which in turn requires REALbasic.

Title: SearchField Plugin 1.0b3 Source
Description: This plugin implements the rounded search field commonly found in applications on Mac OS X. It requires Mac OS X 10.3 both when developing an application and when the final application is run. The control also only works in Mach-O built applications which in turn requires REALbasic.

Title: Selectit
Description:
If you have struggled with the seemingly simple task of making a selection rectangle you will love selectIt!
selectIt uses standard XOR mode drawing to create clean, fast selection rectangles for your graphics type REALbasic applications. The example projects shows just how easy selectIt is to use, with just four methods. selectIt can also be used to create horizontal and vertical splitters and crosshairs. Best of all selectIt is cross platform
Author: Peter Zegelin

Title: Seth's CSV Parser
Description: This pair of classes is designed to be very much like the standard database classes so they should be immediately familiar to you. As far as I've been able to tell from my own testing and feedback from others, this parser works correctly for all correctly formatted CSV files.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: SimpleProgressCanvas
Description: SimpleProgressCanvas 1.0 is a simple replacement for the standard Toolbox progressbar. It doesn't look that fancy and cannot display the "barber pole" but allows to draw text above the bar (like the Netscape progress bar)
Author: Erich Rast

Title: Single Cell Selection Listbox
Description: It's a listbox that can have a single cell selected instead of an entire row.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Sortinterface(Rb1)
Description: A class that implements QuickSort and BubbleSort. It can sort any type of data: You need to subclass this class and then implement a Compare and a Swap function. The Sort class does the rest for you. It comes with lightly documented source and demonstration code.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Spbaudiolib
Description: This module allows RB developers to make toolbox calls to the SoundInputManager
Author: Benjamin J. Schneider

Title: Spinivector
Description: A vector image editing program that does just about everything you could want, including copying, pasting, polygons, béziers etc.
Author: Dan Vanderkam

Title: Splitview
Description: A REALbasic take on the Cocoa NSSplitView class making it ridiculously easy to use and customizable.
Author: Seth Willits

Title: Sslsocket10
Description: Add Secure Socket Layer communication to your REALbasic applications, allowing them to connect to and download data from any secure server on the web. Meant to mimic REALbasic's own Socket control, SSLSocket seamlessly integrates secure sockets for an easy and transparent implementation.
Author: Tristan Perich

Title: Storable Objects
Description: Storable Objects is a package to make storing and retrieving the state of RB classes easy. It consists of a Storable interface class, a StorableStream class, a StorableConstants module and a bunch of storable subclasses of RB controls.
Author: Erich Rast

Title: Supersocket204Demo
Description:
SuperSocket is a networking toolkit for REALbasic. It provides a collection of
classes that can be used to build network-aware applications. SuperSocket enhances
REALbasic's TCP support, and adds new protocols currently unavailable in REALbasic
Author: Essence Software

Title: Tbbutton2
Description: A collection of canvas subclasses which draw several standard Mac OS controls (mostly buttons). These classes can be used to draw standard looking controls seamlessly on top of pictures. There are also new controls to REALbasic such as a small checkbox, small radio, rounded bevel button, and round buttons. Not all of the controls are product-worthy, but with a little work, those that aren't could be.

Title: Bit Ops
Description: Offers you nearly a zillion bit operations on Integers and sets.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: TtCatSearch
Description: This plugin implements the PBCatSearch function of the Mac OS File Manager. This is a very fast routine to find specific types of files on a volume. The MacOS tool Sherlock (aka Find File) uses this function to do its quick search on volumes.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Ttscollectionextension
Description: This plugin adds a method to read back the Keys that are stored in a Collection object, similar to the available "Item" method that returned the values from a Collection.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Ttscrcplugin
Description: This plugin adds methods for calculating CRCs (checksums) in 16 and 32 bit, as well as variably from 16 to 64 bit.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Ttspluginstarter
Description: If you want to write your own plugins, you may use this skeleton. It requires CodeWarrior Pro 4 or higher. It supports 68K, PowerPC, Carbon and Windows x86 code generation.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tts_App_Frame
Description:
Do you need a starting point for a application that uses multiple document windows?
Do you want to maintain a menu that shows a list of the open windows?

Do you have documents that you need to save when closed and thus need to write code that asks the user whether he wants to save, discard or cancel?
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Aliasrecord
Description: The MacAliasRecord plugin provides a class for storing folder and file references in a file (or resource). Very useful when storing FolderItem references in your Preferences file.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Eventmonitor Plugin
Description: Keep track of Events (function keys, idle events) with the EventMonitor class.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Filemgr-Plugin
Description: Identify Volumes and Attributes of files with the FileMgr plugin.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Folderitem Extension
Description: Launch apps in the background, and open documents with the app of your choice with my FolderItem extension class.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Gestalt-Plugin
Description: Inquire many Gestalt Selectors on your Mac using the Gestalt Plugin.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Hidemenubar-Plugin
Description: Need access to the full screen on a Mac? Hide the Menubar and the Control Strip with this plugin.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Icons-Plugin
Description: Convert Icons into Pictures.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: TTs Memory Block Extension
Description: Adds functions to the built-in MemoryBlock class
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Tt_S Macsbug-Plugin
Description: Need to do some Low-Level debugging? Invoke MacsBug from your application.
Author: Thomas Tempelmann

Title: Urleditfield1
Description: URLEditfield is an editfield class that can automatically color links. If you double-click a link, an event gets fired so you can launch the URL. However, this is a fast hack and not suitable for large, scrolling editfields
Author: Erich Rast

Title: Version Tracker
Description: Version Tracker is a socket class based on the httpSocket class by Dan Vanderkamp. It easily enables your application to download version information online and grab an update from the Net if neccessary. Can be used for automatic updates and built-in online news about your application. more info
Author: Erich Rast

Title: Xmlengine
Description: Parse, render, analyse, create and alter XML. Want to make a Mac app that does any of this with XML? You can make it with REALbasic and XML Engine. XML Engine is powerful and simple.
Author: Theodore H.Smith

Title: Zegsruler
Description: ZegsRuler is the fastest and easiest way to add rulers to your REALbasic projects. ZegsRuler supports scaling (zooming), scrolling and changing of the origin as well as lots of control over line length and width, color, background, text etc. In addition, all rulers can be either plain or 3D.
Author: Peter Zegeli

Title: Zegsruler

ZegsRuler supports scaling (zooming), scrolling and changing of the origin as well as lots of control over line length and width, color, background, text etc. In addition, all rulers can be either plain or 3D.
Author: Peter Zegeli
